Papers on Idea and Cause of President Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Today marks the 92nd birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung.
 Rodong Sinmun in an editorial says that Kim Il Sung is a peerlessly great man, an eternal sun who pioneered the sacred cause of Juche and led the progressive humankind along the road of sovereignty and independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last rigorous decade the faith of the army and people of the DPRK in the President's idea and cause has grown stronger. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His cause has a bright future as it has a reliable foundation on which the DPRK can victoriously advance despite any tempest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President lives in the hearts of the army and the people of the DPRK as the supreme brain of the revolution and the sun of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung's idea and cause which recorded the most brilliant page in the history of the Korean revolution and the world revolutionary movement have been fully materialized under the Songun leadership of leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il's Songun cause is a continuation of the revolutionary cause of Juche pioneered and led by the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il set out the Songun politics to successfully accomplish the President's idea and cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last decade covered by the Korean revolution under the banner of Songun was a proud decade during which the revolutionary armed forces and the national power of the country have been remarkably increased true to the President's idea and line of attaching importance to military affairs and a decade of tremendous creation and change when a wide avenue was paved for building a great prosperous powerful nation true to the President's last instructions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has steadfastly maintained the principled stand of defending and carrying forward the revolutionary heritage and traditions of the President 100 percent in the whole period of leading the revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il's Songun revolutionary leadership is characterized by such intense loyalty to the President as doing everything just as he did. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President's leadership mode and art, an all-powerful treasured sword of the revolution and construction, have been carried forward in all fields under Kim Jong Il's Songun leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has led the revolution and construction just the way the President did. Thanks to this leadership all the work of strengthening the party and the army and stepping up the economic and cultural construction has been carried on as intended by the President in his lifetime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il represents the destiny of the DPRK, the heart of the revolution and the eternal banner of victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson editorially stresses that the President's idea and cause will shine long along with the history of the prosperity of the country thanks to the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il, the sun of the 21st century.

Floral Basket Presented to DPRK Embassy in Bangkok 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Thaksin Shinawatra, prime minister of Thailand and leader of the Thai Rak Thai Party, sent a floral basket to the DPRK embassy in the name of himself and his party on April 12 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 A spokesman for the party visited the embassy and laid the basket before the full-length picture of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il before paying tribute to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that Kim Il Sung is the great leader who performed immortal exploits for the happiness of the Korean people, prosperity of the country and the cause of global peace. Kim Il Sung always lives in the hearts of humankind, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the friendly relations between the Thai Rak Thai Party and the Workers' Party of Korea and between the two countries, he expressed expectation that these relations would as ever grow stronger.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from NDFSK Central Committee 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il today received a letter from the Central Committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea (NDFSK) on the occasion of the birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung and the 11th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Lauding Kim Il Sung as the great leader, peerlessly great man and benevolent teacher whom the Korean nation and whole humankind highly worship and praise, the letter said: His whole life is brilliantly recorded with his immortal feats as he successfully accomplished every cause he could for the sovereignty of the country and the prosperity of the nation and brought happiness and glory to the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The human history records famous great men and leaders but does not know such outstanding leader, peerlessly great man as the President who performed the immortal great feats and accumulated a wealth of experience, undergoing all hardships for over 80 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
You have realized the cause of perpetuating the memory of the leader with his Songun politics and let the President's idea and cause shine forever century after century. This is the great feat to be specially recorded in the human history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You have made socialist Korea of Juche demonstrate its might as an ideologically, politically and militarily powerful country, holding high the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The publication of the June 15 joint declaration ushered in an era of the independent national reunification, made it possible to preserve peace on the Korean peninsula and let the global independence become a trend of the times. This is a precious fruition of he Songun politics, Songun leadership of you, the sun of the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter stressed the need for the people from all walks of life to turn out as one in the movement to implement the three charters of national reunification advanced by the President and the June 15 joint declaration provided by Kim Jong Il, realize national cooperation against the U.S. under the banner of the Korean nation-first spirit and build the structure of the nation's confrontation with the United States through practical actions and thus check and frustrate the U.S. moves for Korea's permanent ivision and war against the DPRK and get the U.S. imperialist aggressors withdrawn from this land without fail.

Kim Il Sung's Reminiscences Published Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- More than a decade has passed since the first publication of President Kim Il Sung's reminiscences "With the Century".
 The reminiscences that comprehensively deals with the revolutionary life of the President and exploits performed by him in the struggle has been widely disseminated in over 170 countries in the period, while hundreds of thousands of its copies have been ublished in 18 languages in more than 50 countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 China and Russia published at least 100,000 copies of Vols. 1 to 8 of The Anti-Japanese Revolution from the reminiscences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This biography of the peerlessly great man has been published in national languages to be avidly read by figures of different social standings and other peoples in several countries of Europe including Romania and Bulgaria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 India, Guinea, Nigeria, Mexico and other countries formed organizations to disseminate the reminiscences, while the International Institute of the Juche Idea had Paekbong Library publish its Vols. 1, 2 and 3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seminars on the reminiscences, meetings for presenting impressions of the reminiscences and reading sessions for reminiscences have been held in more than 100 countries including Mongolia, Rwanda, Portugal and Peru. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After reading the reminiscences political, social and academic figures of different countries praised the whole life of Kim Il Sung as the life of the man of great eminence unprecedented in the modern history and the most noble life of a socialist political leader representing the 20th century.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from Chongryon Central Standing Committee 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il today received a letter from the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon).
 The letter said that on the auspicious Day of the Sun the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon paid highest tribute to Generalissimo Kim Il Sung representing the boundless loyalty and reverence of all the officials of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan nd extended highest glory to Kim Jong Il who is carrying forward and carrying out the revolutionary cause of Juche generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It lauded Kim Il Sung whom the Korean people acclaimed and held in high esteem for the first time in the nation's history spanning five thousand years as a brilliant thinker and theoretician, a distinguished statesman, an invincible iron-willed commander, the ather of socialist Korea and benevolent father of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It recalled that he showed loving care and benevolence for Chongryon and the Koreans in Japan, not forgetting them even a moment of his great life, and left precious heritage and exploits for the movement of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that his immortal idea and cause are being creditably carried forward and implemented by Kim Jong Il and the revolutionary cause of Juche has been put on a new higher stage of the Songun era, the letter stressed that thanks to Kim Jong Il, the cause of Kim Il Sung is eternal and the honor and happiness of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan are immense as is the case with the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The officials of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan will uphold and defend Kim Il Sung's Juche-oriented idea of the movement of overseas compatriots and his immortal feats, put further spurs to the seven month-long movement for greeting the 20th Congress of Chongryon and significantly adorning it as a congress of singlehearted unity and a congress of victors and thus bring about a new epochal phase in the accomplishment of the patriotic cause of Chongryon as desired by Kim Jong Il.

Banquet Given by DPRK Government
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- The government of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea gave a banquet at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel on Wednesday on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 Present on invitation were Vishwanath, director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea (IIJI), and his party, a delegation of the Secretariat of the IIJI led by Deputy Secretary General Sakae Araki and delegations of Juche idea study organizations on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and chairman of the Korean Social Scientists Society, in a speech said that the Korean people highly praised the Juche idea followers for fulfilling the noble responsibility they assumed for the era and humankind, remaining true to the faith of Juche despite all the moves of the reactionaries to turn back the orbit of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the expectation that the Juche idea followers would conduct more effective activities for studying and disseminating the Juche idea as required by the new century and make tangible contributions to the struggle of the world people to build an independent, peaceful and prosperous new world free from aggression, war, domination and subjugation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vishwanath in a speech said President Kim Il Sung was the greatest man who performed the immortal feats for the human cause of independence with his outstanding idea and theories and dynamic revolutionary practices and the greatest statesman and leader recognized by the whole world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a great fortune for the world progressive people, the Juche idea followers, in particular, to hold Chairman of the National Defence Commission Kim Jong Il in high esteem as the great leader, he said, reiterating their resolution to conduct positive activities for disseminating the Juche idea and the Songun idea, its embodiment, greatly proud and confident of this, and thus successfully discharge the mission they have assumed before the era and humankind.

Guest Performances Given
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) --Guest performances of the 22nd April Spring Friendship Art Festival were given at various theaters and halls here yesterday.
 Artistes from different countries put on stages immortal revolutionary paeans "Song of General Kim Il Sung" and "Song of General Kim Jong Il" reverberating throughout the world on the occasion of  the birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung (April 15). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Artistes from different countries and overseas Korean artistes staged many songs such as "Star Light", "Let's Present Songs and Dances on the Spring Festival Stage", "We Live, Looking Up to Mt. Paektu", "April Spring Has Come" and " Longing to See Pyongyang" created by themselves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The British art troupe presented an instrumental ensemble of famous song "Nostalgia," the Russian group of famous artistes male solo and the Vietnamese art troupe female trio "Our Leader", the Armenian art troupe female vocal solo "Dear General, Where Are You", the art troupe of  Koreans in China female vocal solo "Cantata to Marshal  Kim Il Sung", the art troupe of Koreans in Australia cello solo "Leader, the Night Is Far Advanced" and other Korean songs were put on stages. This greatly encouraged the Korean people in their efforts to achieve the greatest prosperity of the country under the wise leadership of  Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also staged were colorful numbers including a ballet drama by the Russian ballet troupe, a male vocal solo by the Chinese State Symphony Orchestra and a clarinet solo by the Cuban art troupe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the performances senior officials of the Party and state mounted stages and conveyed floral baskets to the performers congratulating them on their successes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Mongolian art troupe and the German instrumental ensemble separately performed at the Pyongyang International Cinema House and the Yun I sang Music Hall that day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It was appreciated by senior officials of the Party and state, officials of the Party, power bodies, social organizations, ministries and national institutions, heroes, personages of distinguished services, working people, artistes and youth and students in the city, overseas Koreans, diplomatic envoys and members of foreign embassies here and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performances continue.

Tribute Paid to Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Senior officials of the Party, the state and the army, chairpersons of the friendly parties, members of the Cabinet and leading officials of the party and military organs and working people's organizations, servicepersons and people from all walks of life today visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace on the occasion of the Day of the Sun to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung.
 Amid the solemn playing of the immortal revolutionary paean "Song of General  Kim Il Sung" a floral basket was laid before the statue of Kim Il Sung in the joint name of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, the Central Military Commission of the WPK, the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK and the Cabinet of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Senior officials of the Party, the state and the army paid noble homage to him, looking up to his statue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the hall where he lies in state, they made a bow in most humble reverence for him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They went round orders and medals and certificates of honorary titles he was awarded from the DPRK and different countries, his portrait with a sunny smile on his face and bronze relievoes at the Mourning Hall and a train coach he used during his on-site guidance and foreign tour and a car he used in the last period of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also visiting were the chief of the Pyongyang Mission of the National Democratic Front of South Korea, a delegation of Koreans in Japan, delegations of overseas Koreans and other overseas Koreans on a visit to the socialist homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Meanwhile, the foreign diplomatic corps and the military attaches corps here and Vishwanath, director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea (IIJI), and his party, a delegation of the Secretariat of the IIJI led by Deputy Secretary General Sakae Araki and delegations of Juche idea study organizations of different countries on a visit to the DPRK visited the palace to pay homage to the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day foreign delegations participating in the 6th Kimilsungia Festival, a delegation of the Vietnam Union of Friendship Organizations and a delegation of the Russia's Federation of Independent Trade Unions visited the palace to pay homage to Kim Il Sung.

Floral Baskets Laid before Kim Il Sung's Statues
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Floral baskets were laid before the statues of President Kim Il Sung standing across the country today on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 People from all walks of life, servicepersons, youth and students in the capital city mounted Mansu Hill with ardent longing for and boundless reverence for the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen before the statue on the hill was a floral basket sent by  Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of the floral basket-laying music, floral baskets in the name of the party, military and power organs, public organizations, ministries, national institutions, KPA units, scientific, educational, cultural, art, public health and press institutions, factories, farms, schools and others and bunches of flowers and flowers were laid before the statue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also placed there were floral baskets in the name of the unconverted long-term prisoners who are indomitable pro-reunification patriots and the Pyongyang Mission of the National Democratic Front of South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They paid tribute to the President in humble reverence, who performed the great exploits which will shine forever in the annals of the country and the history of the struggle for human emancipation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK Wu Donghe and embassy officials laid a floral basket before the statue of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A delegation of Koreans in Japan, delegations of overseas Koreans and other overseas Koreans, delegations of Juche idea study organizations of Japan, a cultural delegate of Cambodia and participants in the 22nd April Spring Friendship Art Festival laid floral baskets before the statue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Floral baskets were also laid before the statues of the President standing at Kim Il Sung University, Kim Il Sung Military University, the Ministry of People's Security, the Korean Film Studio, the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace and other places of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People, servicepersons, youth and students from across the country visited the statues of the President standing in their residential quarters and laid floral baskets, bunches of flowers and flowers before the statues. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, staff members of the Consulate Generals of China and Russia in Chongjin and delegations of Northeast area of China also visited the statue of the President standing in Chongjin and laid floral baskets and bunches of flowers before the statue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Delegations of Dandong City of China laid floral baskets and bunches of flowers before the statue of the President in Sinuiju.

DPRK on Day of Sun
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- The Democratic People's Republic of Korea is in a festive atmosphere commemorating the Day of the Sun, the most auspicious holiday of the nation.
 Seen in the streets of Pyongyang are boards carrying such words as "Day of the Sun", "Eternal Life", "Commemoration" and "April 15", picture boards, large visual aids and other kinds of decorations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Fluttering on flag poles in streets are red banners, flags of the DPRK, flags of the April Spring Friendship Art Festival and pasted on walls of buildings are posters of the Sixth Kimilsungia Festival and art festival. Trees along streets are ornamented with neon signs and small electric bulbs. 
 Various kinds of flowers including apricot tree flowers delight people enjoying the holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A large number of people are visiting the Kumsusan Memorial Palace and statues of President Kim Il Sung throughout the country to pay deep homage to him. His old home in Mangyongdae is also being visited by many people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 17th International Marathon Race for "Mangyongdae Cup" and meetings of workers and trade union members and youth were held in Pyongyang to vow loyalty to Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il. And the 22nd April Spring Friendship Art Festival, the 6th Kimilsungia Festival, art show of the Songhwa Art Studio and other functions are going on before full houses to commemorate the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Art performances are given at theatres and newly released films screened at cinema houses. Sports games and amusements are being held in all parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Okryu, Chongryu and Sinhung restaurants and other public catering establishments in the capital and local areas are serving traditional spring foods and special dishes to people. Make-shift stands are also crowded with people.

Kim Jong Il Enjoys Performance Given by Art Squad of KPA Unit 324
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, enjoyed a performance given by the art squad of KPA Unit 324.
 The squad put on the stage colorful numbers of various genres including narration and chorus "Thunder on Jong Il Peak", the poetic drama "Let's Remain True to the Faith in the Army to the Last" and chorus "We Will Support the Building of Great Prosperous Powerful Nation with Arms." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers truthfully represented the invincible might of the KPA trained as a matchless army and the unshakable faith and will of the army and people of the DPRK to devotedly defend the headquarters of the revolution and single-heartedly accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche with arms through their performance replete with revolutionary enthusiasm and militant stamina. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance deeply impressed the audience for its high ideological value and artistry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After appreciating the performance full of vivacity and dynamism, he expressed great satisfaction over the splendid performance that clearly represented the noble spiritual world of the servicepersons. He warmly congratulated them on their successful performance and extended thanks to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the art squads of the units have made a great contribution to the education of servicepersons in the days of the Songun politics and achieved leaping progress, he set forth important tasks which would serve as guidelines in further developing mass culture and art among servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also among the audience were KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong, Ri Yong Chol, first vice department director of the Central Committee of the WPK, and servicepersons.

Kim Jong Il Watches Training of KPA Unit 324
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, watched the training of KPA Unit 324.
 He, conducted by the commander of the unit, went round the training apparatuses and facilities of the unit. He dropped in at a military lecture room and saw a tactical training of its commanding officers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted with great satisfaction that the commanding officers of the unit have been trained as competent commanding officers equipped with a high level of operational command capacity to successfully carry out the WPK's Juche-oriented military strategy through strenuous and effective training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He mounted an observation post and watched the training of soldiers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After watching the training of the brave soldiers firmly equipped with the WPK's Juche-oriented combat methods, he highly praised them for their successful training, greatly pleased to see all the soldiers fully prepared themselves politically and ideologically and in military technique to promptly beat back any enemy invasion and firmly defend the socialist homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He learned about the living of the soldiers, going round an education room, a bedroom, a mess hall, a washroom, an outdoor resting place and other places. He stressed the need to take deep care of the living of soldiers so that they might not feel any slightest inconvenience in their living. 
 After seeing the soldiers' pleasant amusement game during break, he praised all of them for leading a revolutionary and militant life full of optimism and conviction of the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave the servicepersons of the unit a pair of binoculars, a machine gun and an automatic rifle as gifts and had a photo session with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The next leg of his inspection was a company of KPA Unit 297. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After watching the soldiers of the company in firepower training, he met with soldiers. He took deep care of their service and living, giving a warm pep talk to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave the company a pair of binoculars, a machine gun and an automatic rifle as gifts and posed for a photograph with its servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Ri Yong Chol, member of the Central Military Commission of the WPK and first vice department director of its Central Committee.
